-- Indian shares continue their record-setting streak; blue chips advance
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Wed Mar 26, 2014 06:10AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, March 26 (Reuters) - Indian shares rose to record highs for a third straight session on Wednesday, as blue chips such as Larsen & Toubro extended recent gains, bolstered by buying from foreign investors on hopes of a recovery in the domestic economy.

The NSE index <.NSEI> rose as much as 0.57 percent to an all-time high of 6,627.45, while the benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> gained 0.53 percent to a lifetime high of 22,172.20. Larsen & Toubro <LART.NS> provisionally rose 2.2 percent, while Tata Motors <TAMO.NS> ended higher 2.4 percent.